[
  "Bom Kim is the founder of e-commerce giant Coupang. ",
  "Mimicking U.S.-based Amazon, Coupang is disrupting South Korea's online retail space by slashing prices and investing heavily in swift deliveries.",
  "In 2016, Coupang raised $1 billion at a $5 billion valuation from Japan's Softbank, headed by its Korean-Japanese founder Masayoshi Son.",
  "In November 2018, it raised $2 billion from the Softbank Vision Fund with a $9 billion valuation, making it Korea's most valuable startup. ",
  "Kim worked at Boston Consulting Group before founding Vintage Media Company, which he sold in 2009. He started Coupang the next year."
